    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hand tools for pulling poles from the ground consisting of two serrated jaws that rotate around a spindle, the two halves connected to each other with a chain. In hop growing, pole extraction pliers are used in combination with a lever to pull stakes from the earth.</Note_Text>
